      "content": "I can't give you medical advice, but for a short burst to boost your Vitamin D, 50,000 IU daily is a high dose and should be discussed with a doctor, especially since you're trying to jumpstart things. While some people claim it works, taking that much without knowing your baseline can be risky. A doctor can properly assess your needs and tell you the safest, most effective way to get those levels up.",
